

   For the Variscite Board:   DART-MX8M
-----------------------------------------------


     make_rootfs.sh:    makes a ubuntu rootfs

     make_Yrootfs.sh:   makes a Yocto rootfs

     make_sdcard.sh:    burns rootfs to sdcard (works for both ubuntu and Yocto)


 Before using the scripts above:
 -------------------------------

  Follow directions from the Variscite wiki page:


  https://variwiki.com/index.php?title=Debian_Build_Release&release=RELEASE_BUSTER_V3.0_DART-MX8M


  You don't need to do everything.   Use these steps:

  1.  git clone https://github.com/varigit/debian-var.git -b debian_buster_var02 debian_imx8mq-var-dart

  2.  cd ~/debian_imx8mq-var-dart

  3.  MACHINE=imx8mq-var-dart ./var_make_debian.sh -c deploy

  4.  sudo MACHINE=imx8mq-var-dart ./var_make_debian.sh -c bootloader

  5.  sudo MACHINE=imx8mq-var-dart ./var_make_debian.sh -c kernel


---------------------------

    dtb's used by Variscite imx8

         fsl-imx8mq-var-dart.dtb -> fsl-imx8mq-var-dart-sd-lvds.dtb

---------------------------

    ttymxc1:

         Device RxD to Pin 4
                TxD to Pin 6
                GND to Pin 12

    For getty:

         /etc/systemd/system/getty.target.wants


    ttymxc1:

         Device RxD to Pin 4
                TxD to Pin 6
                GND to Pin 12














